Why is canned tuna so cheap when fresh tuna is so expensive? 

Tuna salad:
- Tuna+mayo+salt+yogurt+lime
- Red coral lettuce 
- Baby cos lettuce 
- Butterhead lettuce
- Fresh shallots 
- Goji berries 
- Spring onions 
- Hard boiled egg 

Well it basically comes down to what is described as "sushinomics". Tuna that is canned are species that reproduce quickly creating a vast supply (albacore, yellowtail etc.) But are considered less tasty. The ones that are used for sashimi and sushi are the Bluefin tuna which not only require more efforts in catch but are also low in supply. With the fish only reaching reproductive at 8 years and only having a life span of around 40 years, there aren't much to go around. Overfishing has also greatly contributed to the decline in supply of bluefins as they are being caught before being able to reproduce. Lack in regulation will likely lead to extinction of these tasty swimmers. Luckily there are efforts being put forward and the status of bluefin have been reduce from endangered to least concern. Which is great but it needs to be continued because they taste so good ü•∫.

Oh and side note: if you dont want to add alot of mayo to your tuna; sub with unsweetened yogurt, lime and salt. Gives it a fresh taste and adds a 'lil probiotics to you diet.

ASSEMBLE üçΩ DON‚ÄôT COOK ü§ç

Truth, I am not at all a great cook‚Ä¶but I am creative, and I love to cook.

I did not grow up with a refined palate but did have a mother and grandmother who loved to 'bung it together', as my mum Margot would say. And so, as I developed a love for all things food, I had to start by instinct. I must also confess that I'm terribly lazy and am always trying to find the simple route of favourite dishes. Even the most delicious meals I make rarely take more time than they need to. This is why I follow a simple rule. Assemble the dinner, but don't try to cook it.

We're inundated with perfection these days. Scroll through your Instagram and see how many plates of food have the perfect basil leaf cocked on the perfect forkful of pasta. I would be frustrated to create a meal like this; nobody has time for that!

Instead, I don't sweat it. My dinners are platters of messy sauces and imperfectly cut veggies. I will cook grains and throw on top whatever needs to be used up from the veg crisper in my refrigerator. 

I write this story because on the weekend, In an attempt to impress, I went against my rule and attempted to follow a recipe. LOL.. it was a fail. Place me in a bustling environment of chatter and champers, and well‚Ä¶ let's just say I am not great at Muti-tasking. I now know never to go against what makes me feel comfortable in my kitchen. 

I chalk my mistakes up to one word: rustic. Instead, I make what feels good to make, what gets my hands dirty, and what shows the season's colours. Instead, I tear basil leaves with my hands and call it a day.

Whether you are a right or left-brain thinker who doesn't (or does) love cooking, no worries‚Ä¶ the trick is to assemble, not cook. Simplify, and you will be healthier and less stressed for it.

These Creamy, Lemony Cucumber Sandwiches are perfect for lunches, get togethers and parties! üçãü•í They‚Äôre super easy to make in advance and taste incredible! ‚ú®

Save this post! Full recipe below! üëá

Ingredients: 

4 oz whole cream cheese, softened to room temp
2 TB chopped fresh dill
Zest and Juice of half a large lemon
Salted butter, softened for spreading on bread slices
kosher salt
freshly ground black pepper
6 slices high quality white or whole grain bread
1/2 large cucumber, seeded and thinly sliced, thoroughly dried with paper towels

Instructions: 

Combine: in a small bowl, combine cream cheese, fresh dill, lemon zest, and lemon juice. Add enough kosher salt and pepper to taste.

Assemble: butter each slice of bread (prevents sogginess.) Lay slices with butter-side-up on a work surface. Evenly distribute the cream cheese mixture onto each slice. Arrange towel-dried cucumber slices on top of the first 3 slices of bread. Top with remaining bread. Slice off the crusts. If not serving immediately, wrap tightly in cling wrap and chill for up to 24 hours.
Slice: when ready to serve, slice into 4 triangles per sandwich. Cover and chill any leftovers.

This peanut butter banana smoothie recipe is DELICIOUS and it‚Äôs really simple to make! Make this quick and healthy snack in less than 5 minutes!

Ingredients
2 bananas
2 cups ice
1 cup milk
1/2 cup greek yogurt plain
2 Tablespoons peanut butter heaping
1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Instructions
Chop the bananas into smaller pieces. Or at the very least, break it in half.
Add all of the ingredients to the blender, adding the ice last.
Blend the ingredients until smooth.
Top your smoothie with melted peanut butter and/or banana pieces. (optional)
Enjoy!

Hi besties! I thought it was time I‚Äôd share one of my all time favorite recipes. It‚Äôs a deliciously creamy coconut curry that I‚Äôve been making for a couple of years now. It‚Äôs the perfect comfort food in my opinion. 

THAI RED COCONUT CURRY CHICKEN
(ft my sous chef @izza.rehman & photographer @sa_herrr)
Ingredients:
* 1 pound thinly sliced chicken thighs 
* 1 jar Maesri red curry paste
* 2 tbsp lemongrass paste plus a teaspoon of fresh minced lemongrass 
* 1-2 diced shallots 
* 2 minced garlic cloves
* About an inch of minced ginger
*2 thinly sliced bell peppers 
* 1 can coconut milk
* 1 can coconut cream 
* 1 tbsp fish sauce (optional)
* a few Kaffir lime leaves 
* 2 tbsp brown sugar 
* 2 minced Thai chilies 
* 1/2 - 1 juiced lime
* 1/4 cup chopped Thai basil
*1/4 cup toasted cashews

-In a large pan, brown your chicken over medium high heat until no longer pink.
-Add your red curry paste along with the fresh lemongrass and lemongrass paste, garlic, ginger and shallot. Mix with the chicken and saut√© until aromatic. 
-Add your bell peppers and cook for a couple of more minutes and then bring the heat down to medium and add your coconut milk and cream. Let it simmer for a couple of minutes and then add the kaffir lime leaves, Thai chilies and brown sugar. 
-Stir well and cook for a few more minutes and then take off heat. 
-Add your Thai basil, toasted cashews and lime juice and serve over rice. Enjoy!

Understanding portion sizes can be really difficult as most of us learn this in our formative years from our parents. Unless you seek formal education yourself, you‚Äôre more than likely to continue on with what you‚Äôve been taught. On top of that, 
diet culture and the media certainly influence us to believe that smaller portions = healthier. All of which neglects the most important part, NUTRIENTS. Irrespective of portion size, if your meal consistently lacks key nutrients or fails to fuel your body, then it‚Äôs irrelevant. 

Now, I will say this. YES portion size matters when looking at weight loss and fitness / macro goals. üèÉüèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

YES you can have a portion size that is too large if it makes you feel too full and uncomfortable. ü§¢

YES you can have a portion size that is too small. E.g. if you‚Äôre left feeling hungry after eating (not enough food or enough calorie / nutrient dense foods) ü§ï

Key messages üîë
- eat to fuel your body 
- listen to your hunger cues 
- ensure your plate has adequate nutrients

 Easy coconut chickpea curry 
.
Get the recipe below by @happyskinkitchen : 
Recipe: 1 can of chickpeas
1/2 can of coconut milk 
1/2 can of chopped tomatoes 
1 onion ‚Äì finely chopped 
2-3 garlic cloves ‚Äì minced 
1 tsp of turmeric powder 
1/2 tsp of chilli powder
1 tsp of curry powder 
Salt to taste 
To serve: rice and veggies of your choice

Add a dash of oil to a large pan and once hot add in the chopped onion. Fry the onion gently for 3-4 minutes until it starts to caramelised. Add in all the spices + the garlic cloves. Cook for another minute and continue stirring to avoid burning. Add a dash of water to prevent from sticking. Add in the drained chickpeas, coconut milk and tinned tomatoes. Mix everything together, add bit of boiling water just to enough to cover the chickpeas. Put the lid on an cook on a low heat for 20-25 minutes. Serve with some rice and veggies.

*FULL RECIPE*
Here's the recipe for the Jamaican Jerk chicken with coconut rice and mango salsa that I made for dinner last night. This is a one pot recipe, so minimal cleaning up! 

JAMAICAN JERK CHICKEN WITH COCONUT RICE AND MANGO SALSA

You're going to need:
(For 3 Servings)
3 Diced Chicken Breasts
210g Rice 
2 Chopped Red Onions
1 Chopped Red Peppers
1 Diced Mango
2 tbsp Lime Juice
2 tbsp @schwartz.uk Jamaican Jerk Seasoning
1 tsp Ground Coriander
1 1/2 tsp Garlic Granules
300ml @alpro Coconut Milk
300ml Chicken Stock

1. Coat your chicken in the @schwartz.uk Jamaican Jerk seasoning and fry until fully cooked.
2. Add in 1 onion, 1 tbsp of lime juice and the garlic granules, mix well and fry for a further 5 minutes.
3. Wash your rice then add to the pan with the chicken, frying for a minute to toast it.
4. Add in the @alpro coconut milk and chicken stock, bring to the boil, reduce the heat then cover and simmer for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the rice is cooked. 
5. Meanwhile, mix the other onion, red pepper, mango, 1 tbsp lime juice and the coriander together to form your mango salsa.
6. Once cooked, top the chicjen and rice with the salsa and enjoy!

Let me know in the comments if you try this recipe and what you think of it!

Looking for a fast recipe to make for lunch? This dish is light and can be made in only 25 minutes!

‚ú®Bok Choy with Tamari Sauce‚ú®

Ingredients:
‚úÖ2 lb bok choy, small 
‚úÖ1 Tbs ginger, fresh, minced
‚úÖ 1/4 cup scallions, thinly sliced 
‚úÖ1 1/2 Tbs olive oil, divided ‚úÖ6 Tbs tamari sauce 
‚úÖ1 Tbs hemp seeds 

Directions:
Prep : 
1. Trim bok choy bottoms and cut in half lengthwise. 
2. Mince ginger. 
3. Slice scallions. 

Make :
1. Coat bottom of pan with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil, over medium-high heat. When hot, lay bok choy in single layer, cut side down (do not overcrowd). Add 2 tablespoons water and cover about 2 minutes. 

2. Lift out of pan, drain, and place on platter. Remove water from pan and repeat with remaining bok choy. Leave residual water in pan. 

3. Add 1 tablespoon oil and ginger to pan and cook, stirring over high 
heat until ginger is browned. Remove from heat and add tamari sauce. 

4. Pour sauce over bok choy, sprinkle with scallions and hemp seeds.

I‚Äôm a fritter lover‚Ä¶ save this post to try this version - Fennel Seed, Courgette, Corn and Smoked Chilli 

This makes for the perfect speedy and satisfying dinner alongside a fresh green salad üçΩ 

Any left overs? Pack them for lunch or warm them up another evening (keep in the fridge for up to 4 days) ‚úÖ 

Want something gluten free? Simply substitute the flour for either self raising GF flour, almond mehl or chickpea flour üòç

Ok enough chit chat - you‚Äôll need ‚ú® 

1 tsp fennel seeds 
2 large courgettes, grated 
2 spring onions, finely sliced
2 tsp baking powder 
1 tsp salt 
400 grams corn kennels 
2 tbsp coriander, finely chopped
1 1/2 tsp smoked chilli flakes
3/4 cup flour
1/2 cup breadcrumbs 
1 cup canola oil for frying 
Coriander, lime and mayo to serve 

Method
In a morale and pestle, crush the fennel seeds.

Place the grated courgettes, spring onions, salt, corn kennels, coriander, crushed fennel seeds and smoked chilli flakes into a large mixing bowl. Mix well.

Add the flour and breadcrumbs along with 1 tablespoon of water to help emulsify.

Heat 1/3 of the oil in a non stick pan. Once hot and using an ice cream scoop, spoon into the oil. Fill the. Pan but do not over crowd. Press down a little too flatten so you have flat bottom but fluffy fritters. cook until golden on high heat and flip, cooking until golden and crunchy again. Remove and drain excess oil onto paper towel.

Heat another 1/3 of the oil and repeat.

To serve, place crunchy fritters onto a serving platter, mayo into a small serving bowl and I like to top with extra virgin olive oil and a sprinkle of sea salt. Finish with lime wedges and coriander

Recipe:
60 grams oatmeal
2 tsp chiaseed
100 ml milk

1 tbs caramel paste melted

Prepping:
Mix the oatmeal, chiaseed and milk.
Put it in the fridge overnight.

Simply means Spaghetti with Oil & Garlic. This is such a simple but beautifully delicate & delicious dish.

‚ú® CALLING ALL PASTA LOVERS ‚ú®

Serves 2
Ingredients- 

- 6 tbsp extra Virgin Olive Oil @bertollioliveoiluk for me!
- 8 garlic cloves finely sliced
- 200g pasta- spaghetti or linguine
- Handful fresh parsley, finely chopped
- Salt, 1/2 Tsp
- 1/2 Tsp Black pepper- fresh ground
- Parmesan- (optional 50-80g)

In a pan add cold water heavily salted and bring to a boil. 

In a large non stick frying pan add the oil lightly heat, the key to this dish is to slowly bring the garlic to temperature without burning and allowing it to go lightly golden brown. Add the sliced garlic and ensure it doesn‚Äôt sizzle, just a low heat is fine. 

Add the pasta to the salted water and boil.
Once your kitchen smells like an authentic Italian restaurant or my dads kitchen üßÑ (extra garlic on everything) add the cooked pasta directly from the pan so it brings with it the salted pasta water, also add the freshly chopped parsley, salt, pepper & grated parmesan.

Turn off the heat and gently fold the pasta until the liquid emulsifies and goes creamy and delicious, add more pasta water if needed. 

Parmesan isn‚Äôt traditional, but sure as hell is an incredible addition and one I wouldn‚Äôt miss, especially if you‚Äôre having a glass of red with it ü§§üç∑üç¥

This one is bowl licking good. 

Much Love,
Jade x

Ce ziceti de un chec cu crema de fistic, cu afine si picatele de ciocolata? Pregatiti-va pentru cea mai simpla si mai faina reteta de chec. E gata in 40 de minute cu tot cu timpul de coacere. üòâ

Ingrediente
2 oua

Crema de fistic in combinatie cu ciocolata si cu afinele e de vis. Nu ratati reteta asta ca nu exista una mai simpla. In loc de pasta de fistic se poate folosi inclusiv unt de arahide indulcit.

üòÇSeriously though, who can relate!? Our need for carbs when we are stressed is hardwired into us..

When we are stressed, we are spending time in a state within the nervous system called 'sympathetic' or 'fight or flight' This state is ruled by cortisol and adrenaline, your stress hormones. 

On the other side of things we have the 'parasympathetic nervous state' which is when we are relaxed, calm, not stress eating cakes. This state is ruled by dopamine and GABA, our calm, relaxed hormones. 

Just as we can have low levels of things like iron and so eat red meat or a take an iron supplement to try to boost our levels, we can have lower levels of dopamine or GABA.

These low levels can impact us more so at certain times of the month than others... Before a period/during menopause our progesterone levels are at a very low point, which means we have less GABA/Dopamine circulating than usual. So our bodies will try to 'help' us with getting us to eat cakes, carbs or chocolate which help us create a little hit of dopamine. 

While it feels good in the moment, it usually means our blood sugar sky rockets and then we end up feeling groggy, tired and grumpy when it comes back down again. High blood sugar also impacts our nervous system, so we can get a bit stuck in a cycle of sorts.

So what's a girl to do when life isn't fair and cake is the answer?! Here's a few tips:

üí´ Pair sugar with protein/fat e.g. nuts, seeds
üí´ Taking 4 deep breaths in, hold for 4 and release for 4 seconds engages the vagus nerve and surpasses cortisol release
üí´ Consider a magnesium glycinate supplement (speak to doc first if you take any meds) 
üí´ Stop having caffeine on an empty stomach - it is spiking your cortisol and contributing to your stress eating. Instead have decaf or have food first

Cooking in the summer is ridiculously easy. A little bit of prep work in the morning, let the flavours come together while your meat and veggies marinate all day, fire up the grill that night, and within 20 minutes, your gourmet meal is ready.

Lamb is one of my favourite meats because it is tender and juicy, especially when cooked to medium-rare. While I am a massive fan of a rack of lamb, this was my first attempt at cooking a leg of lamb. I have grown accustomed to ordering lamb kebabs when I'm out to dinner because I'm not sure I'm patient enough for the long slow roasting process.

This lamb kebab recipe was perfect because (aside from the 30 minutes it took to break it down- it was my first time, don't judge!), the rest was super quick and easy. The pomegranate molasses bring a tart tang that complements the lamb's earthy flavour, and the fresh mint helps balance out the sweetness.

This week we are continuing on with another delicious and also healthy Mexican meal plan with our Chicken Tacos, Pico de Gallo and a crunchy and colourful Mexican Bean Salad.‚Å†
‚Å†
Click the link in our bio @granluchito or see below for recipe.‚Å†
‚Å†
Ingredients - ‚Å†
Chicken:‚Å†
500g /1.1 lbs of chicken breasts‚Å†
2 teaspoons Gran Luchito Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix‚Å†
1 lime (juice)‚Å†
2 tablespoons olive oil‚Å†
Salt and freshly ground black pepper (for seasoning)‚Å†
‚Å†
Guacamole:‚Å†
2 ripe avocados‚Å†
¬Ω red onion (finely diced)‚Å†
1 jalape√±o (finely chopped)‚Å†
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil‚Å†
‚Å†
Pico de Gallo:‚Å†
2 vine tomatoes (diced)‚Å†
¬Ω red onion (finely diced)‚Å†
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil‚Å†
1 lime (juice)‚Å†
1 handful of coriander (roughly chopped)‚Å†
‚Å†
To Serve:‚Å†
6 Gran Luchito Soft Tacos Wraps‚Å†
‚Å†
How to make it - ‚Å†
1. Add the Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix onto your chicken breasts with the lime juice, 1 tablespoon of olive oil, a pinch of salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cover with cling film and let it marinate for 20 mins at least.‚Å†
2. In the meantime prepare a quick guacamole. Add the avocado flesh into a bowl and mash it with a fork. Add the onion, jalapeno, extra virgin olive oil, a pinch of salt and black pepper, then mix and set aside.‚Å†
3. In a different bowl prepare a quick pico de gallo. Mix the tomatoes, onion, extra virgin olive oil, lime juice, coriander, salt and pepper.‚Å†
4. Get the barbecue going or heat up a cast-iron skillet with the remaining olive oil. Grill or pan-fry your marinated chicken and let it get a bit of colour on both sides. Finish cooking it covered with a lid, to allow it to cook fully without getting dry.‚Å†
5. Once ready, remove from the heat and cut the chicken into strips with a sharp knife. Serve your chicken with warm Soft Taco Wraps, a good amount of guacamole and some of the pico de gallo. Finally don‚Äôt forget to try some Gran Luchito Salsas!

Shaved Steak & Asiago Sandwich (15 min prep-to-table)
1. Mince fresh garlic. Add olive oil to pan and roast garlic, leaving slightly raw.
2. Add sliced onions to oil and cook until tender. Salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
3. Add shaved flank steak to pan. Season with garlic, cracked black pepper, and salt. Cook to medium rare. Remove from heat. 
4. Butter sourdough bread. Spread pesto on one side, garlic truffle aioli on the other.
5. Begin frying bread on pan. Add shaved parmesan and Asiago cheese to one side.
6. As cheese starts to melt, add steak and onions on one slice of bread. Top with cheese and close slices.
7. Roast both sides of sandwich equally.
8. Serve with side salad with balsamic vinaigrette and enjoy!

Garden fresh deconstructed zucchini boat casserole‚ù§Ô∏è This was seriously soooo deliciousüòã 

Preheat oven to 350- Saut√© diced onionsüßÖpeppersü´ëand a few cloves of garlic chopped in a pan with a little bit of olive oilüíö Add in your ground meat and continue cooking until meat is cooked throughüëåüèª Season with salt, pepper & Italian seasoning, mix in half a small can of diced drained fire roasted tomatoesüçÖ You could just do the whole can if you like but I knew that my kiddos wouldn‚Äôt like it with too many tomatoesüòâ Next, Lightly grease a casserole dish, add a little tomato sauce first, slice up your zucchini into round medallions and layer onto sauce, sprinkle a little black pepper and grated parmesan, next top with meat mixture, add a little more fresh grated parmesan, top with fresh shredded mozzarella cheese and garnish with some fresh chopped basil. ‚†Ä
This dish is a perfect light dinner for the warm weather we‚Äôve been having and so easy to cook with hardly any ingredients needed! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Ingredients:‚†Ä
üçÖ1 chicken breast‚†Ä
üçÖ1 ball mozarella cheese ‚†Ä
üçÖ2 tomatoes ‚†Ä
üçÖsmall handful of basil ‚†Ä
üçÖpesto ‚†Ä
üçÖbalsamic glaze ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
For the chicken: ‚†Ä
preheat the oven to 180 degrees ‚†Ä
Chop your tomatoes ans mozarella into even slices ‚†Ä
Cut slices into the chicken breast deep enough for the stuffing ‚†Ä
Place the chicken breast on the oven tray and place slices of mozarella and tomato into the slices made in the chicken ‚†Ä
Top with 2 teaspoons of pesto, salt & pepper‚†Ä
Cook in the oven for roughly 30 mins till the chicken is cooked through ‚†Ä
Top with fresh basil & serve ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
For the caprese salad:‚†Ä
Lay out even slices of tomato and mozarella on your plate ‚†Ä
Lightly drizzle olive oil & balsamic glaze‚†Ä
Top with salt, pepper & fresh basil ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Enjoy! ‚†Ä

BOLU JADUL 3 WARNA
Loyang tulban uk 24x9cm
Oleh: @yulichia88

Bahan:
375 gram mentega (aku blueband dan butter wijsman)
275 gram gula halus KIS @chefmatechocolate
250 gram terigu protein rendah
35 gram susu bubuk
60 gram susu kental manis
Vanili secukupnya
10 kuning telur
4 putih telur
Secukupnya Cocoa Powder @chefmatechocolate pasta mocca, pasta coklat 

Cara:
1. Kocok mentega dan gula halus Kis, vanili hingga mengembang
2. Lalu masukkan kuning telur satu persatu mixer rata, masukkan susu kental manis sambil trus dimixer
3. Masukkan susu bubuk dan terigu yg sdh diayak terlebih dahulu, sambil dimixer rata dgn kecepatan rendah
4. Mixer putih telur hingga mengembang kaku
5. Campur ke adonan kuning diaduk rata menggunakan Spatula 
6. Bagi adonan 3 bagian ( mocca, coklat dan plain) utk adonan mocca, tambahkan 1 sdt terigu dan utk adonan coklat, tambahkan 1sdm Cocoa Powder dan sedikit pasta coklat, lalu tuang ke cetakan( caranya bisa liat di video ya, postingan sebelah ya üëâ)
7. Panggang di oven yg sdh dipanaskan terlebih dahulu, suhu awal 160¬∞c api bawah 25 menit lalu set api atas bawah turunkan suhu 150¬∞c  panggang smp matang, tergantung oven masing2 ya, biar aman lakukan test tusuk ya, jika adonan msh menempel di alat tusukan berarti kuenya blm mateng

üçö This rice hack will CHANGE your LIFE.

Post by @foodess

Instead of precisely measuring your rice and water and hoping for the best, simply fill a large pot with water as you would for pasta.

Add rice and cook at a low boil until soft. Strain for a couple of minutes in a colander. You'll get fluffy, separate grains - or in other words, perfect rice, every time!

WHAT TO COOK - literally ANY GRAIN, not just rice. Quinoa, barley, amaranth, millet - you name it, it can be done this way. WHY have we been making our lives more difficult all this time?

HOW LONG TO COOK - it depends on the rice/grain variety. Start testing doneness about 5 minutes sooner than it takes making it according to package instructions (my white basmati takes about 15 minutes).

HOW MUCH SALT - add 2 tsp kosher salt per litre/quart of water for perfectly-seasoned rice (or pasta, potatoes, etc.), or use half that amount if you prefer barely-seasoned grains as a blank canvas.

üå∫ *LEMON BUTTER KEBAABS*
üå∫

"Rec & pic cred: @mama_taught_me_well
Ruhana Ebrahim

Picture credit : @cook.with.sumz 

INGREDIENTS
Kebabs-
¬Ω kg mutton mince (washed and drained)
1 onion (grated, liquid squeezed out)
2 slices bread (freshly ground)
1 teaspoon salt
¬Ω teaspoon white pepper
1 teaspoon dhana Jeeru (Cumin) (coriander cumin) powder
1 tablespoon ground garlic paste
1 teaspoon ground green chillies
¬º bunch fresh coriander (chopped)

Sauce-
60g butter/rama margarine
1 tablespoon ground garlic paste
¬Ω teaspoon dried mixed herbs
Pinch dhana Jeeru (Cumin) powder
1 teaspoon Aromat (a South African Spice) spice
2 tablespoon flour
1 cup fresh cream
3-4 tablespoon lemon juice

METHOD
Kebabs-
1. Mix everything together.
2. Form round balls with greased hands, the size of a golf ball.
3. Place in the fridge to firm up.
4. Heat a little oil in pot, place kebabs in and cook till browned all over and cooked through.
5. Leave aside.

Sauce-
1. Melt butter in a frying pan.
2. Add flour and whisk to form a smooth roux.
3. Add garlic and braiss for a few seconds.
4. Add in spices and lemon juice, whisk in.
5. Pour in cream and whisk till smooth.
6. Bring sauce to a gentle boil and simmer till sauce thickens.
7. Switch off heat.
8. With a slotted spoon, remove kebabs from pot and place into sauce.
9. Allow to heat together.
10. Do not overcook sauce as it may split.
#mamataughtmewellrecipes

INFO & TIPS

Frog Eye Salad
Ingredients
1 cup sugar
2 tablespoons all-purpose flour
1/2 teaspoon salt
1-3/4 cups unsweetened pineapple juice
2 large eggs, lightly beaten
1 tablespoon lemon juice
1 package (16 ounces) acini di pepe pasta
3 cans (11 ounces each) mandarin oranges, drained
2 cans (20 ounces each) pineapple chunks, drained
1 can (20 ounces) crushed pineapple, drained
1 cup miniature marshmallows
1 cup sweetened shredded coconut
1 carton (12 ounces) frozen whipped topping, thawed
Maraschino cherries, optional

Directions
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt. Gradually stir in pineapple juice. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Stir a small amount of hot mixture into eggs; return all to the pan, stirring constantly. Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir 2 minutes longer. Remove from the heat. Gently stir in lemon juice.
Transfer to a large bowl. Cool to room temperature without stirring. Cover surface of dressing with waxed paper; refrigerate until cooled.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water. Place in a very large bowl; stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows, coconut and dressing. Fold in whipped topping. Cover and refrigerate until chilled. If desired, garnish with cherries.

Source: Taste of Home

Ayam Masak Merah

1/2 chicken
3 shallots
2 garlic
1 lemongrass
3 sekawan (Cinnamon Stick, Cloves and Cardamom)
1 tbsp chilli paste
3 tbsp tomato sauce
2 tbsp chilli sauce
1/4 cup evaporated milk
1/4 cup green peas 

1. Fry chicken with salt and turmeric. Set aside. 
2. Blend shallots and garlic. Saut√© with lemongrass until fragrant. 
3. Add in chilli paste with 1 tsp of sugar. Cook until the oil separates (pecah minyak). Add water if needed. 
4. Add in tomato and chilli sauces with some water. Simmer until sauce thickens. 
5. Add in evaporated milk and mix until homogenous before adding in the fried chicken. 
6. Add in green peas before turning off the heat.

The easiest strawberry shortcake ever! 
Steps:
1. Mix all of the cake ingredients together in a mug
2. Microwave for 4 minutes
3. Mix filling together and slice strawberries

5. Place mug on a plate and slice in half
6. Top one half with filing and strawberries, place second half on top, and pile on the rest of the filling and strawberries
7. DIG IN!!!

This peanut butter banana smoothie recipe is DELICIOUS and it‚Äôs really simple to make! Make this quick and healthy snack in less than 5 minutes!

Ingredients
2 bananas
2 cups ice
1 cup milk
1/2 cup greek yogurt plain
2 Tablespoons peanut butter heaping
1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Instructions
Chop the bananas into smaller pieces. Or at the very least, break it in half.
Add all of the ingredients to the blender, adding the ice last.
Blend the ingredients until smooth.
Top your smoothie with melted peanut butter and/or banana pieces. (optional)
Enjoy!

Boscaiola! @rumourhasit9 had cooked this for my family and I and It‚Äôs now my go too for family meals. It‚Äôs a clean pasta that‚Äôs not too heavy, not too light and full of goodies.

Ingredients:
8 oz any mushrooms you can find
5-7 slices of prosciutto
1/3 cup sun dried tomato
1/4 cup white wine
2-3 sprigs of thyme
1 cup heavy cream
3 cloves garlic
2 Tbsp parsley
1 Tbsp butter
1/2 cup parmesan
12 oz pasta of choice
Optional: Chili flakes to your liking

-Finely chop your garlic, parsley, sun dried tomato, and thyme. -Thinly slice mushrooms and prosciutto.
-In a sauce pan on medium heat, add some oil and cook mushrooms till brown (5-7 mins). 
-Season with salt and pepper, then add a Tbsp of butter.
-Add the prosciutto. Once heated through add the garlic and chili flakes.
-Toss in the sun dried tomatoes and thyme, then deglaze with white wine.
-Once the white wine has reduced significantly, add the heavy cream and mix. 
-Let the flavors get to know each other then add your cooked pasta, parmesan and parsley.
-Give it a good mix, add some pasta water to thin out the sauce if needed.
-Serve and enjoy! üçù

CHOCOLATE BAKED OATS üòã I love chocolate and I love cake - they‚Äôre the two things that in the past would usually let me down when I tried to follow a healthy eating regime. Thanks to all the inspiration here I‚Äôm finding ways to still have my cake and eat it (lol!) while not undoing my hard work. I baked this last night to eat this morning and it was yummy! It works out as 4 syns and 320 calories per portion. Recipe below - I made this for me and my husband, so just half the ingredients if it‚Äôs just for one personüîª

Ingredients:
16 Aero chocolate melts - 8 melts per person at 1/2 syn per melt (4 syns per portion)
80g oats (40g = 1 HEXb)
60ml semi skimmed milk (1/4 HEXa)
1/3 cup zero calorie sweetener (free)
2 eggs (free)
2 tsp vanilla essence (free)
1 tsp baking powder 

1. Preheat your oven at gas mark 5/6 or 180 degrees Celsius. Grease a baking dish with cooking spray.
2. Blitz your oats in a food processor and then mix into a bowl with 1/3 cup sweetener and 1 tsp baking powder.
3. Crack 2 eggs into the bowl and mix thoroughly.
4. Add 2 tsp vanilla essence and 60ml of semi skimmed milk and stir the batter again.
5. Fold in 16 Aero melts - 8 melts per portion is 4 syns.
6. Pop into the oven for half an hour or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Leave to cool before eating!

PARMESAN & GARLIC FRIES 

These were next level, absolutely unreal.. bursting with flavour, and so easy to make. 

First off follow the below recipe for the perfect chips. 

When your chips are cooked pop them aside and get a large high sided pan and drop in a good size knob of butter, you want it to melt and cover the base of the pan. 

Crush 3 garlic cloves and drop into the butter as it starts to melt. Keep on a medium heat for a minute or two and then drop your cooked chips in then pan along with a good shake of grated parmesan.. stir / shake and get them all coated. 

Shake over some dill and a little salt and pepper to serve. üî• 

Perfect Airfryer Chips

*Don‚Äôt worry, if you haven‚Äôt got an airfryer you can use the oven (same temp 180). 

Serves 4
1kg potatoes
Low-calorie spray oil
 
1 - Wash and peel your spuds and cut into chips. I like mine chunky but do them the way you like, whether it‚Äôs wedges or skinnier French fries.

2 - Pop them in a microwave-safe bowl and give them a good rinse under the tap, then drain ALL the water off; this is very important.

3 - Pop them in the microwave and cook on full power for 12‚Äì13 minutes (less if making a smaller batch), giving them a good shake halfway through. You want them to be soft to the touch, but not mushy. Don‚Äôt worry if they stick, this is just the starch; you can rinse them again in cold water after microwaving and this will unstick them.

4 - At this point you can season with paprika or garlic granules, but I like mine plain and simple.

5 - Next pop them into the airfryer at 200¬∞C. It will take roughly 15‚Äì20 minutes to get them nice and golden, but pay attention to our special trick.

6 - Every 5 minutes I open the basket and give the chips a little spray with my oil and a good shake. This ensures they all cook evenly and end up super crispy from the oil. If I‚Äôm cooking for a gang and I have to make a few batches, I leave the made ones in a bowl and just as my last batch is ready I throw them all back in together to heat them up.

Ingredients: 

‚àô 2 medium zucchini (about 1¬Ω lb.), halved lengthwise
‚àô About 1 lb Adagio¬Æ Eggplants , cut into 1" wedges
‚àô ¬æ cup extra-virgin olive oil, divided

Instructions:

1. Prepare a grill for medium heat. Toss zucchini, eggplant, and ¬º cup oil on a rimmed baking sheet; season with 1 tsp. salt and ¬Ω tsp. pepper. Grill, turning often, until steamy, tender, and charred all over, 8‚Äì12 minutes. Return to the baking sheet and let cool.

2. Cook pasta according to package directions.

3. Slice grilled vegetables into bite-size pieces and transfer to a large bowl. Add tomato, cheese, vinegar, thyme, and 1¬Ω tsp. salt, ¬Ω tsp. pepper, and ¬Ω cup oil and mix to combine. Drain pasta and immediately add to the bowl with vegetables. Mix well to combine, then top with basil.

Super easy blueberry overnight oats!

Ingredients:
- ‚Öî cup rolled oats

- ¬Ω cup vanilla greek yogurt
- ¬Ω teaspoon vanilla extract
- 1 teaspoon chia seed, optional
- ¬Ω teaspoon cinnamon
- 2 teaspoons of something sweet like honey, berry jam, or maple syrup
- handful of fresh blueberries

Directions:

Quick garlicky oyster sauce ground pork with silky egg

Recipe: 
2 lbs. ground pork 
1 bulb garlic, chopped
1 large onion, diced
1 thumb ginger 
12-15 eggs, scrambled
Salt to taste
Sriracha to taste 
4 tbsp ish oyster sauce 
1 tsp chicken bouillon 

A) Over med-high heat, cook onion and ginger until aromatic. Season with salt as you go. 

B) Add ground pork, season, and let cook until the juices evaporate off. Add garlic, sriracha, oyster sauce, and chicken bouillon, making sure they make as little contact with the bottom of the pan as possible. Do Not Stir. Let sit until the pork and onion mixture caramelizes. Check progress by looking at pieces on the outer most edge of the pan. 

C) Once the pork and onion are caramelized (crusty and browned), turn the heat to high and let it sit for a minute. Then, stir everything together quickly. After combining, turn the heat off and continue mixing for another minute. Mix in softly scrambled eggs and serve over rice.

Macro Friendly Chicken Enchiladas ü•ë 

Ingredients:
Whipped FF cream cheese, 80 g
Salsa Verde, 60 g (1/4 cup)
1 Tbs lime juice
1 tsp chili powder
1/2 tsp cumin
1/2 tsp onion powder
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/3 cup cilantro
Green onions, as much as desired
2 cups shredded chicken (Any kind you want! Great if you have leftovers from a different night. In this photo, I used an HEB rotisserie chicken!)
10 extra thin mission corn tortillas
1 can red enchilada sauce
3 oz lite Mexican cheese

Directions:
(1) Mix your cream cheese, salsa verde, lime juice, and all the seasonings together. Add in cilantro, green onions, & shredded/diced chicken. Combine.

(2) Warm your corn tortillas in the microwave for 10 to 15 seconds until flexible. Divide the chicken and cream cheese mixture evenly amongst the 10 tortillas. Place them seem side down in a greased baking dish.

(3) Cover the enchiladas with the sauce & shredded cheese. Bake it for 25 for about 10-15 min. 

Serve hot! The guacamole shown is not included in the macros but it‚Äôs highly encouraged as an add-on üòò.

Cals: 168

Tabbouleh (1 hr prep-to-table)
1. Wash and chop fresh parsley into fine pieces.
2. Dice baby tomatoes into fine pieces.
3. Dice cucumbers into small pieces. 
4. Cut green onions into fine pieces.
5. Slice mint into fine pieces.
6. Add ingredients into a large bowl. Add olive oil and fresh minced garlic.
7. Squeeze half a lemon in. Press and mix with hands, taking care to express the juices. Ideally, let sit for 15 min-overnight.
8. Add couscous, mix, and serve!

Simply means Spaghetti with Oil & Garlic. This is such a simple but beautifully delicate & delicious dish.

‚ú® CALLING ALL PASTA LOVERS ‚ú®

Serves 2
Ingredients- 

- 6 tbsp extra Virgin Olive Oil @bertollioliveoiluk for me!
- 8 garlic cloves finely sliced
- 200g pasta- spaghetti or linguine
- Handful fresh parsley, finely chopped
- Salt, 1/2 Tsp
- 1/2 Tsp Black pepper- fresh ground
- Parmesan- (optional 50-80g)

In a pan add cold water heavily salted and bring to a boil. 

In a large non stick frying pan add the oil lightly heat, the key to this dish is to slowly bring the garlic to temperature without burning and allowing it to go lightly golden brown. Add the sliced garlic and ensure it doesn‚Äôt sizzle, just a low heat is fine. 

Add the pasta to the salted water and boil.
Once your kitchen smells like an authentic Italian restaurant or my dads kitchen üßÑ (extra garlic on everything) add the cooked pasta directly from the pan so it brings with it the salted pasta water, also add the freshly chopped parsley, salt, pepper & grated parmesan.

Turn off the heat and gently fold the pasta until the liquid emulsifies and goes creamy and delicious, add more pasta water if needed. 

Parmesan isn‚Äôt traditional, but sure as hell is an incredible addition and one I wouldn‚Äôt miss, especially if you‚Äôre having a glass of red with it ü§§üç∑üç¥

This one is bowl licking good.

1 package (17.3 ounces) frozen puff pastry, thawed
1 package (10 ounces) frozen chopped spinach, thawed and squeezed dry
4 ounces cream cheese, softened
1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese
2 large eggs, divided use
2 garlic cloves, minced
1/2 teaspoon pepper
1/4 teaspoon salt

Directions
Preheat oven to 400¬∞. Unfold puff pastry; cut each sheet into 12 sections. Place in greased mini muffin cups, pressing gently onto bottoms and up sides, allowing corners to point up.
In a large bowl, stir together spinach, cream cheese, mozzarella, feta, 1 egg, garlic, pepper and salt. Spoon 1 tablespoon into each cup. Bring pastry corners together and pinch to seal. In a small bowl, beat remaining egg. Brush over pastry edges. Bake until puffed and golden brown, about 20 minutes.

Instagram reels are the key to gaining growth on the platform so its crucial to know how to successfully create one. Here‚Äôs how:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Use On-Screen Text and Captions - Adding on-screen text and subtitles to your videos is a no-brainer when it comes to reaching more users. Plus, not only are subtitles great for people who watch without sound, but they‚Äôre invaluable for those with hearing difficulties.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Use Trends as Inspiration - Similar to TikTok, Reels come and go quite quickly. To hop on a trend before it becomes old news, take a few minutes each morning to scroll through the Instagram Reels tab and other creators‚Äô profiles to see what they‚Äôre sharing. Is there anything that seems to consistently pop up ‚Äî a particular song? An audio clip? A dance trend? If so, click on the music to see how many other creators have used the audio. Scroll through the videos to get an idea of what the trend is.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Drive Traffic by Encouraging Viewers to Head to Your Link in Bio - The best way to drive traffic from Reels is by including a clear call-to-action (CTA) that encourages people to head to your link in bio. This could be with on-screen text placement, a verbal call-out, in your video caption, or all of the above. You can also use a link in the bio tool to create a mini landing page with multiple link buttons and clickable images.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Find Your Niche and Post Consistently - One of the best ways to gain virality on Instagram Reels is by finding your niche and posting consistently. There are so many Instagram users with a wide range of interests and hobbies. No matter what your brand or business does, there‚Äôs a niche for you!

5Ô∏è‚É£ Include 3-5 Hashtags - Including 3-5 hashtags can be a great way to help the Instagram algorithm ‚Äúunderstand‚Äù your content and serve it to relevant audiences. For example, using hashtags like #easyrecipes, #mealideas and #dinnerinspiration will indicate to the Instagram Reels algorithm that your content is about food ‚Äî which may increase the likelihood of it being served to users who are actively engaging with similar content.

Cheesy Ancho Queso Sausage and Pasta

Looking for an easy weeknight dish? This Easy Cheesy Ancho Queso Sausage and Pasta üëÜüèªis SO yummy, cheesy and has a delicious little kick to it too. üå∂

Featuring the Ancho Queso Chicken Sausage from @gilbertscraftsausages, you are definitely going to want to ‚ú®SAVE‚ú® this #recipe for later this week, or next! It's a great one to have in your recipe arsenal! üôåüèª

WHAT YOU NEED:
üßÄ 12 ounces elbow pasta (we used @eatgoodwheat), 3 tbsp unsalted butter, 3 tbsp flour, 1 tsp sweet paprika, 1/2 tsp onion powder, 1/4 tsp garlic powder, 24 ounces evaporated milk, 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese plus about 1/4 cup more for topping, 1/4 cup parmesan cheese, 1 package (4 links) Gilbert's Ancho Queso Chicken Sausages, 1/4 cup panko breadcrumbs, 2 tbsp butter (melted), and chopped chives as desired

HOW YOU MAKE IT:
üßÄ Start off by pre-heating your oven to 375 degrees.
üßÄ Cook elbows according to package directions. Drain and set aside.
üßÄ While pasta cooks, coin sausage links and then saut√© in pan over medium heat for a couple of minutes, until slightly browned. Remove from heat and set aside.
üßÄ In a large pot, melt butter. Then whisk in: flour, paprika, onion and garlic powders. Cook for 1- 2 min.
üßÄ Next, whisk in milk, a little at a time. Cook until sauce begins to thicken. Then, remove from heat.
üßÄ Stir in only 2 cups cheddar cheese as well as parmesan.
üßÄ Add in pasta and stir to combine. Then add in sausage coins and again, stir to coat.
üßÄ Transfer macaroni mixture to a pan (we used a 9.5 x 9.5 square) and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese. Set aside.
üßÄ Combine breadcrumbs and melted butter. Then sprinkle coated breadcrumbs over top of the cheese.
üßÄ Bake at 375 degrees for 20- 25 minutes. Once done, remove from oven.
üßÄ Garnish with chives and enjoy!

Cheesy corn dip

Nici nu are sens sa va explic cat de bun poate fi acest sos de branza si porumb (inspirat de la @halfbakedharvest ). Un sos cremos de cheddar combinat cu boabe de porumb dulci si crocante se prelinge incet si fin pe o bucata crocanta de chips din lipie cu parmezan‚Ä¶take my money! Salvati-va reteta pt urmatorul movie night, beer night, date night sau ati inteles voi, any kinda‚Äô night. O sa va placa. 

Ingrediente:
- 300 g boabe de porumb fiert (poate fi din conserva, congelat si fiert, sau taiat direct de pe »ôtiulete)
- 1 ceapa mica spre medie taiata marunt
- 1 ardei gras verde taiat marunt (sau galben, dar nu rosu)
- 200g crema de branza 
- 100-150g smanatana dulce (depinde de consistenta ei, cat e de lichida)
- 100 g cheddar rosu razuit (se gaseste in Mega, Lidl, Auchan, Carrefour, etc)
- Condimente: 1 lgt rasa de pudra de usturoi, 2 lgt boia afumata, sare si piper dupa gust
- Servire: coriandru proaspat sau patrunjel, fulgi de chilli, jalape√±o proaspat sau murat, lipie sau tortilla chips

Cum procedati?
‚úîÔ∏èCaliti ceapa pt cateva minute apoi ardeiul gras. Nu le caliti prea tare, sa nu fie prea moi. 
‚úîÔ∏èAdaugati boabele de porumb fierte si mai lasati pe foc cateva minute amestecand. 
‚úîÔ∏èUrmeaza sa puneti peste legume crema de branza si smantana. Amestecati si gatiti pana se omogenizeaza si totul devine cremos.
‚úîÔ∏èLa final adaugati si condimentele si branza cheddar. Amestecati pe foc pana branza e complet topita si cremoasa. 
‚úîÔ∏èTurnati continutul intr-un bol si deasupra coriandrul/patrunjelul proaspat, fulgii de chilli si rondele de jalape√±o.
‚ÄºÔ∏èSe serveste obligatiu cald, imediat ce e gata. Pregatiti intai chipsurile apoi dip-ul.

üìåEu am pregatit pe langa acest dip niste chipsuri din lipii. Am uns 3 lipii cu ulei de masline si am presarat deasupra pudra de usturoi. Am taiat lipiile in chipsuri triunghiulare (relativ ü§î practic doar le-am ciopartit cum am apucat). Le-am asezat in tava, am presarar parmezan ras peste ele si le-am copt pt cateva minute la 180 grade. Dar paziti cuptorul sa nu se arda. Doar cateva minute. 
Swipe pana la final pt un pont.

W E E T B I X  S L I C E

So here's my version of Weetbix Slice for all those folks who messaged me for the recipe after seeing my stories...not many slices left to take a good photo, as it doesn't last long in our house.

BASE

In a bowl...
4 Weetbix - crushed
1 1/3 cup All purpose flour (plain) 
3/4 cup sugar (I like to use coconut sugar but white is fine) 
6 teaspoons unsweetened cocoa powder
2 teaspoons baking powder 
1/2 cup desiccated coconut 
100gms dark chocolate - break-up 
200gms butter - melt 
2 teaspoons vanilla extract

GANACHE 

1 1/2 cup icing sugar 
6 teaspoons unsweetened cocoa powder 
Desiccated coconut 
1 teaspoon vanilla extract 
6 teaspoons butter - melted 
Milk 

MAKE

‚ñ™Ô∏éLine 20x20 baking tin
‚ñ™Ô∏éIn bowl add weetbix, flour, sugar, cocoa, desiccated coconut + baking powder
‚ñ™Ô∏éMelt dark chocolate + butter on low till blended then and add vanilla extract 
‚ñ™Ô∏éPour melted mix into dry ingredients and mix well
‚ñ™Ô∏é Pour mix into lined baking tray and press firmly + evenly down
‚ñ™Ô∏é Place on middle shelf in pre-warmed med oven and bake for 10-15mins. Don't over cook or your slice will be dry.
‚ñ™Ô∏é Cool down in pan and add ganache

MAKE GANACHE

In a bowl, sift icing sugar + cocoa powder then add vanilla extract and melted butter. Begin to mix and slowly add milk till your desired whippiness. Make sure you blend all the lumps out. Spread onto cooled slice and sprinkle with desiccated coconut. Cut slice into desired size and EAT! 

Best kept in airtight container in the fridge.

PS...I like to add nuts into the base or sprinkle chopped up + toasted macadamia nuts on top for crunch. Or you can even add those scrappy bits of cereal or muesli into your base...the options are endless!

**Spoiler alert : contains courgette recipe**

It's that time of year again.  Too many courgettes = hunt for new recipesüîçü§¶üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

Found this one in a Turkish recipe book in the local library. Easy to make & really tasty so thought we'd share. 

Courgette Fritters (makes c. 10 fritters)
Ingredients
400g courgette, trimmed and coarsely grated
¬Ω tsp salt
2 tbsp olive oil
¬Ω onion, finely chopped
1 garlic clove, finely chopped
55g plain flour, sifted
¬Ω tsp baking powder
1¬Ω eggs, lightly beaten
115g feta cheese, crumbled
5g flat-leaf parsley, chopped
Greek-style yoghurt, to serve

Instructions
Place the grated courgette in a colander, sprinkle with the salt and toss to mix. Set aside for 20 mins. 
Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil in a large frying pan over a medium heat. Add the onion and the garlic and cook for 6-7 minutes, until softened. Remove as much liquid as possible from the grated courgette by squeezing it with your hands, then add it to the pan to cook, stirring for another 4-5 minutes, or until the courgette starts to colour (our courgettes didn‚Äôt really colour but the end result was still delicious). Remove from the heat to a large bowl and allow to cool slightly. 
Add the flour, baking powder, egg, feta and parsley to the bowl and stir well. Season. 
Heat the remaining olive oil in a clean non-stick pan over a medium heat. Cook heaped tablespoons of the courgette mixture, in batches, for 3-4 minutes on each side, or until deep golden. Drain well on paper towels before serving with the yoghurt. 
¬†
From a Turkish recipe book by Leanne Kitchen.

Shaved Steak & Asiago Sandwich (15 min prep-to-table)
1. Mince fresh garlic. Add olive oil to pan and roast garlic, leaving slightly raw.
2. Add sliced onions to oil and cook until tender. Salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
3. Add shaved flank steak to pan. Season with garlic, cracked black pepper, and salt. Cook to medium rare. Remove from heat. 
4. Butter sourdough bread. Spread pesto on one side, garlic truffle aioli on the other.
5. Begin frying bread on pan. Add shaved parmesan and Asiago cheese to one side.
6. As cheese starts to melt, add steak and onions on one slice of bread. Top with cheese and close slices.
7. Roast both sides of sandwich equally.
8. Serve with side salad with balsamic vinaigrette and enjoy!

-4 minced cloves garlic

Flip when bubbles appear.

üå∂Ô∏èüçùüçÖ CHILLI BUTTER TOMATO SPAGHETTI üçÖüçùüå∂Ô∏è Long time no pasta, so just dropping by with a taste of the Med right here ü§§ü§§ A fresh tomato sauce, simmered with garlic and chilli, lotttts of butter, and served with fresh pasta. So much flavour with (mostly) store cupboard ingredients, and ready in 20 - perfect for summer evenings ‚òÄÔ∏è‚òÄÔ∏è I like mine extra saucy and extra buttery, so feel free to bump up your ingredients to suit your taste üëåüèºüëåüèº

Chilli Butter Tomato Spaghetti (serves 2):

150g spaghetti
50g unsalted butter
1/2 red onion, finely chopped
350g cherry/baby plum tomatoes, halved
2 x garlic cloves, sliced
1/2 x teaspoon sea salt (may need more, adjust to taste)
1/2 x teaspoon chilli flakes
1 x tablespoon apple cider vinegar (I used @willysacv)
1/2 teaspoon sugar
Freshly cracked black pepper
Small handful parsley, chopped
50g Parmesan, grated

Cook spaghetti according to pack instructions. Save a ladle of pasta water for the sauce.

On a medium high heat, add the butter to a large saucepan and gently fry the onions for 2-3 minutes. Add the tomato halves and fry for 4-5 minutes. Add the garlic, ACV, sugar, salt, chilli, and continue to cook until the tomatoes soften and release their juices (about another 5-10 minutes). Squish the tomatoes with the back of a wooden spoon to break apart. Add enough reserved pasta water to loosen the sauce (about 50ml), the cooked spaghetti, half the parmesan and the parsley, and combine well. Season with pepper, more salt if required, and serve with the remaining parmesan on top üëåüèºüëåüèº

‚ú®COLLAGEN CHALLENGE...

Collagen is a protein found in muscles, tendons, skin, ligaments, and bones. It makes up about 30% to 40% of proteins in the human body.  As we get older our bodies make less of it and lower quality collagen. Skin becomes thinner and sags while ligaments lose their elasticity, joints get stiffer and much more. 

As our bodies begin to lose collagen from 30 it‚Äôs essential we make sure we are getting enough collagen. The effects become noticeable after several years. Even though this is a natural process, it‚Äôs possible to accelerate & slow down collagen loss. 

The below can interupt and reduce natural collagen production: 
üçî Consuming too much sugary food and refined carbs 
üö¨ Smoking 
‚òÄÔ∏è Exposure to UV rays 
üí¶ Pollution

As the amount of collagen decreases, other parts of your body suffer as well:
üëâ Bones ‚Äì become weaker and more fragile
üëâ Joints ‚Äì cartilage wears out, causing pain & making it tough to stay active
üëâ Muscles ‚Äì function decreases affecting mobility and balance

Collagen can be found in many foods and also supplements! I love @vitalproteins.uk 

Foods such as:
üç£Fish with skin on
üçóChicken bones 
üç≥Egg whites 
üçãFruits and veg, such as citrus fruits, berries, tropical fruits, leafy greens, peppers and tomatoes

This Chocolate Pancake  is a must try for all chocolate lovers. 

Use Trust range of sugars for the perfect balance of sweetness and taste.

Repost @homecookingshow

Ingredients:
-Maida - 1 1/3 Cup
-Cocoa Powder - 4 Tbsp
-Baking Powder - 2 Tsp
-Sugar - 3 Tbsp
-Chocolate Chip - 2 Tbsp
-Salt - 1/4 Tsp
-Egg - 1 No.
-Milk - 1 Cup
-Melted Butter - 1/4 Cup
-Vanilla Essence - 1/4 Tsp
-Milk - 1/4 Cup
-Butter

Chocolate ganache
-Fresh Cream - 1/2 Cup
-Milk - 1/4 Cup
-Semi-sweet Cooking Chocolate - 100 Gms

Method:
-To make pancakes
-In a medium bowl whisk together egg until creamy. Add in milk and melted butter, and whisk until combined well.
-In another bowl whisk dry ingredients and add them into the wet ingredients. Whisk until combined well. It will be a thick batter. Fold in chocolate chips.
- Heat a pan over medium heat and either spread a little butter over it.
- Scoop the batter onto the pan using a 1/4 cup for each pancake.
- Cook until you see bubbles on the top, for about 1 minute or so.
-Flip them over and cook for another 1 minute.
-Transfer to a serving plate and repeat with the remaining batter.
-Serve pancakes with chocolate ganache

To make the Chocolate Ganache
-Heat heavy cream and milk in a saucepan.
-Add chocolate chunks and stir well until it turns into a smooth and silky ganache.
-Wait until it reaches room temperature before pouring it over pancakes

You‚Äôll have so MUCH-ROOM in your heart for this Baked Creamy MUSH-Room! üíìüòç

Baked Creamy Mushrooms Recipe:
Butter - 3 tbsp + For greasing 
Garlic (finely chopped) - 1 tbsp
Onion (finely chopped) - 1 no
Thyme (finely chopped) - 1 tsp
Mushroom (diced) - 400 grams
Maida - ¬º Cup
Milk - 500 ml
Salt - ¬º tsp
Black Pepper Powder - A pinch
Cheese (grated) - ¬º Cup
Bread (cubes) - 10 - 15 nos
Mozzarella Cheese (grated) - ¬Ω Cup

Cooking Instructions:

1. Heat a pan, and add butter. Let it melt
2. Add the chopped garlic and saute till it turns light brown
3. Add the onions and thyme and saute till it turns translucent
4. Add the mushrooms and saute for 3-4 minutes.
5. Add maida and mix till the mushrooms are coated with the maida and mix it till the maida is rid of the raw flavour
6. Add and mix till the maida is dissolved in the milk and keep mixing it till the mixture starts to thicken
7. Add salt, pepper, and fresh cream and mix it well. 
8. Add grated cheese finally and mix well. Bring the mixture to a soft boil
9. Transfer the mixture to an oven-safe bowl
10. Add bread cubes to it and press it in a little.
11. Top it off with mozzarella and bake it in the oven till the cheese turns brown

Let talk easy peasy meals! Last week was a write off for me and meal prepping. First week back from vaca and I needed to get back into the groove of things! ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã

This is one of my go to meal prep recipes! Super simple and quick! I always precut the broccoli and precook the quinoa and shrimp (or chicken), which will be good in the fridge for 3 days. ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
- 1 cup of broccoli‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
- 6-8 shrimps‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
- 1/3 or 1/2 cup of quinoa‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
- Coconut Oil (or any oil you have)‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
- Spices of your choice (I use Peg City Seasoning from Spice World and chili powder) ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
Put a bit of oil in a pan and add the broccoli, I usually add a lid to cook a bit faster.‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
After about 5 minutes and stirring between, add the shrimp (may need a bit more oil to not stick).‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
Stir in between and add quinoa after about 3 minutes.‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
Add spices - I don't measure, just go by taste.‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
Mix it all up to get the spices over everything and heat the quinoa.‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã
Put it in a bowl, and time to eat! ‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã

This peanut butter banana smoothie recipe is DELICIOUS and it‚Äôs really simple to make! Make this quick and healthy snack in less than 5 minutes!

Ingredients
2 bananas
2 cups ice
1 cup milk
1/2 cup greek yogurt plain
2 Tablespoons peanut butter heaping
1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Instructions
Chop the bananas into smaller pieces. Or at the very least, break it in half.
Add all of the ingredients to the blender, adding the ice last.
Blend the ingredients until smooth.
Top your smoothie with melted peanut butter and/or banana pieces. (optional)
Enjoy!

INGREDIENTS ‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è
1.5 lb. boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into 2-inch pieces
1 Tbsp olive oil, or avocado oil
1 tsp dried oregano
1 tsp dried thyme
1 tsp cayenne
sea salt and fresh ground black pepper to taste, about 1/4 teaspoon each

For the Tzatziki dip:
1 cup plain whole Greek yogurt
1/2 cup seeded, grated cucumber
3 Tbsps chopped fresh dill
2 Tbsps fresh lemon juice
3 fresh garlic cloves, minced
sea salt and fresh ground black pepper to taste

INSTRUCTIONS ‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è
Start by making your Tzatziki dip: combine all ingredients in a bowl/jar, taste test, adjust as desired, then refrigerate until ready to use.

If using wooden skewers, allow them to begin soaking in water for at least 20 minutes, to prevent burning.

Next, preheat your grill to medium-high.

In a medium bowl, add your chicken pieces and sprinkle with oregano, thyme, cayenne, sea salt and pepper, then drizzle with oil, and toss and stir well to coat.

Thread 2-3 pieces of chicken onto each skewer, then arrange them on the grill with some space in between each skewer.

Close the grill lid and cook for about 7 minutes until chicken is cooked through, flipping them a couple of times during cooking time.

Serve skewers with Tzatziki dip, lemon wedges, and your favorite fresh chopped veggies!.

Ingredients:

Method:
‚úîIn a pan, saut√© chopped mushrooms with some butter till slightly brown and set aside to cool

INGREDIENTS
12 boneless, skinless chicken thighs (about 950g | 2lbs)
Salt and pepper to taste
2 tbsp coconut oil
2 cups broccoli florets
1 cup light chicken stock
2 tbsp balsamic vinegar
1 tbsp Dijon mustard
1 tbsp tapioca starch
1 tsp chili pepper flakes
.
.
INSTRUCTIONS
Sprinkle the chicken thighs with salt and pepper and then melt the coconut oil in a large, skillet set over high heat. When the pan is hot enough, add the pieces of chicken, nice-looking side down, and cook them without moving them for about 4 minutes, until they turn opaque about half way up and develop a nice golden crust. Flip the pieces of chicken and cook them for another 3 to 4 minutes, until the meat is cooked all the way through and the juices run clear. Remove to a plate.
Put the skillet back over the heat source, lower the heat to medium and add the broccoli. Cook it for about 3 minutes, until slightly softened.

Meanwhile, mix the chicken stock, vinegar, mustard, chili pepper flakes and tapioca starch together in a large glass measuring cup or other container, preferably one that is equipped with a spout.
Pour this over the broccoli as soon as it‚Äôs cooked to your liking; bring to the boil and continue cooking until the sauce thickens

Chimichurri Crispy Potatoes ü•î by @alwayshungryinlondon

Smokey bites of potato heaven with a spicy chimichurri sauce. 

Potatoes:
10 baby potatoes
1tbsp olive oil
1/2tsp cumin seeds
1tsp sweet smoked paprika 
pinch of sea salt 

Chimichurri: 
1 fat clove of garlic
1 red chilli
Handful of parsley 
2tsp chopped fresh oregano 
Salt and pepper 
Extra virgin olive oil & white vinegar 

Preheat the oven to 200 degrees c. Parboil the potatoes. Place potatoes on baking tray and lightly crush them. Add the oil and spices. Roast for 20 minutes or until crispy. 
Finely chop the herbs, garlic and chilli. Add the oil and vinegar 3:1 ratio and season to taste. 
Remove potatoes from the oven and enjoy with copious amounts of chimichurri. 

Enjoy!

These #airfryer Salmon skewers with a chimichurri dressing are perfect for a lighter Summer meal and so easy to make at home! 

Serves 2:
2 salmon fillets cut into cubes 
1 courgette, peeled into ribbons
1 yellow pepper, diced 
Seasoning: 1tbsp olive oil, 1tsp garlic powder, 1tsp dried oregano, 1tsp smoked paprika

Salad: 
Shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, cucumber, feta, sumac, lemon juice and extra virgin olive oil 

Chimichurri recipe:
Handful of fresh parsley, finely chopped
2tsp fresh oregano, chopped
1tsp dried oregano 
2 garlic cloves, finely chopped
1/2tsp dried chilli flakes
1/2 fresh red chilli, finely chopped
1/2tsp sea salt & black pepper
3tbsp extra virgin olive oil
1tbsp white wine vinegar 

Preheat airfryer to 200 degrees c. Make your skewers with the salmon, courgette ribbons and peppers and coat in the seasoning. 

Make your chimichurri and salad. 

Cook the salmon skewers for 8 minutes in the airfryer or roast them in a hot oven at 200 degrees for 12-15 minutes. 

Enjoy!

Instant pick-me-up

Are you feeling stressed, anxious, tired or all of the above? How about an instant pick-me-up in the form of a detoxifying juice to help beat the holiday blues?

Sometimes we don't have time or the appetite to eat all the healthy vegetables and fruits, so freshly made juices can be a brilliant addition to a healthy diet.

Beetroots, carrots and pineapples are excellent ingredients for a quick pick-me-up juice, and they are all packed full of nutrients and deliciousness.

Beetroots are a good source of vitamins and minerals, such as folate, manganese, iron, vitamin C, boron, silica and potassium. Furthermore, they are high in several beneficial plant compounds, mainly betaine, vulgaxanthin and inorganic nitrates (which are associated with reduced blood pressure). Not only can beetroots lower blood pressure, they can also improve oxygen use, stamina and exercise performance. Beetroots are also high in fibre, which is a good thing, but please note that they also have FODMAPs, which for some can cause digestive problems.

Carrots are also packed full of nutrients and are a good source of beta carotene, vitamin K1, fibre, potassium and antioxidants. Carrots have many health benefits and they have been linked to weight loss, lowered cholesterol and improved eye health.

Then we have pineapples - an ubebu favourite! They are also loaded with nutrients and vitamins, such as vitamin C, manganese, copper and vitamin B6. Additionally, they contain disease-fighting antioxidants and they have been found to ease digestion and arthritis and boost immunity.

Wow, these were incredible and so filling - I got the recipe Inspo from my girl @slimming_teganxx page ‚ù§Ô∏è

Ingredients (1 portion):
- 1 large potato (mine was 330g)
- 1/2 onion
- 2 bacon rashers
- 50g sweetcorn
- 30g low fat cream cheese
- 30g low fat cheese
- Spring onion & parsley to serve

Method (45 mins ish):

1. Pierce the potato with a knife in serval place and pop your potato in the microwave for 10 mins, then wrap in foil with a few sprays of oil and put in the oven/airfryer for 20-30mins

2. Meanwhile in a pan cook your onions and bacon, once cooked add to a mixing bowl with the sweetcorn and cream cheese 

3. Once the potato is cooked, cut in half and scoop out the middle and put in the mixing bowl, mix everything together then scoop back into the skins

4. Top with cheese and put back in the oven/ under the grill until melted, serve with some spring onions & parsley 

I served with the rainbow salad from @aldiuk with a tbsp of @aldiuk Caesar dressing (see pic 3)

Let‚Äôs hear it for the creamy curry‚Äôs in the back üì£ This was such a fantastic simple dinner which hit all the right warming belly spots!ü•∫

* INGREDIENTS *
- Chicken Breast Fillets (I used 300g for 2 portions)
- 1 tbsp Cumin 
- 1 tbsp Medium Curry Powder
- 1 tsp Ground Coriander 
- 1 tsp Turmeric 
- 2 tbsp Ground Almonds 
- 250ml Chicken Stock 
- 3 tbsp Light Soft Cheese 

* METHOD *
- Coat the chicken in all spices and ground almond. 
- Put chicken into an oven proof dish and cover with dissolved chicken stock. 
- Cook at around 180 degrees for 1 hour. 
- Remove from the oven and mix in the soft cheese and sprinkle over more ground almond. 
- Cook for a further 30 minutes until sauce has thickened and ground almond has browned. 

Served with a side of Basmati Rice and enjoy!

Ce ziceti de un chec cu crema de fistic, cu afine si picatele de ciocolata? Pregatiti-va pentru cea mai simpla si mai faina reteta de chec. E gata in 40 de minute cu tot cu timpul de coacere. üòâ
Save/comment/‚ù§Ô∏è

Ingrediente
2 oua
2 lingurite zdravene de miere de albine
40 ml ulei neutru
200 g pasta de fistic indulcita
80 ml lapte
160 g faina de prajituri
1 praf de sare
4 g praf de copt
40 g picatele de ciocolata
40 g afine

Intai de toate preincalzim cuptorul la 180 de grade apoi facem aluatul. 

Intr-un vas incapator amestecam toate ingredientele umede pana se omogenizeaza bine apoi adaugam ingredientele uscate cernute. Omogenizam si turnam in tava tapetata cu hartie de copt. Deasupra presaram afinele spalate si uscate bine. 

Se coace la 170 de grade pentru aproximativ 30 de minute. Testul cu scobitoarea e de ajutor. 

Crema de fistic in combinatie cu ciocolata si cu afinele e de vis. Nu ratati reteta asta ca nu exista una mai simpla. In loc de pasta de fistic se poate folosi inclusiv unt de arahide indulcit.

Ingredients:

1/2 lb. farfalle
1 medium yellow onion, finely chopped
1 tsp olive oil
3 large garlic cloves, minced
4 plant based sausages (396 g)
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
1 tsp dried parsley
1/2 tsp dried oregano
1 cup (packed) baby spinach
1 cup canned crushed tomatoes
1 cup dairy free heavy cream

Instructions:

Cook farfalle in salted water according to package directions, reserving 1/4 cup of the cooking water prior to draining.

Meanwhile, preheat large pan on medium heat. Add onions and oil, cook on medium low for 10 min, adding 1/2 cup water to prevent burning if needed and stirring periodically. Add minced garlic and crumble in the sausages. Stir, add all the seasonings, and cook for 6 to 8 min, stirring periodically, until starting to brown. Add remaining ingredients and cook 2 to 3 min, stirring as spinach wilts. Add pasta, stir, add pasta cooking water if desired. Serve with red chili flakes and basil if desired.

Finally got round to making baba ganoush! Not sure why but I thought it was going to be way more effort than it was. TASTED UNBELIEVABLE ü§§ no blender needed. 

Ingredients: 
2 aubergines 
2 minced garlic cloves 
2 tablespoons lemon juice 
1/4 cup tahini 
1/3 cup olive oil 
2 tbsp chopped flat leaf parsley
1/4 tsp cumin 
Salt n peps 
Sprinkle of paprika 

Method:
~ preheat oven to 230 degrees c 
~ chop your aubergines in half lengthwise and brush cut sides with olive oil 
~ place them skin side up on baking paper lined tray and bake in oven for 35-40 mins 
~ when done, scoop out aubergine flesh and strain flesh to get rid of liquid 
~ put in bowl, add garlic and lemon juice, and whisk with a fork to break down the aubergine 
~ add tahini and stir till combined 
~ while stirring, slowly drizzle in olive oil 
~ once all broken down and mixed together, add in salt, cumin and parsley 
~ add more lemon juice to taste 
~ transfer to a pretty bowl and drizzle with more olive oil and a sprinkle of paprika and parsley 

Voila! I chopped up some pitta breads and roasted them in olive oil, salt n peps and rosemary to scoop up the deliciousness with.

INGREDIENTS:

- 20g Hazelnuts, blanched
- 200g Purple sprouting broccoli, trimmed of its thick stalks
- ¬Ω Red onion, thinly sliced (approx. 75g)

METHOD:
1. Boil the potatoes until cooked, approx. 15 minutes, then drain.
2. Make a garlic paste by smashing it with salt with the back of your knife. Add to the picked herbs and the anchovies and chop finely. Put in a bowl and mix with the mustard, lemon juice, olive oil and black pepper.
3. Toast the hazelnuts in a dry pan for a few minutes. Use a pestle and mortar or similar to coarsely crush the hazelnuts.
4. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in the same frying pan. Add the broccoli and sliced onion and a splash of water. Cover and saut√©/steam until broccoli cooked al dente. Remove lid and boil off any water left in pan. Season and empty into large bowl.
5. Thickly slice the potatoes and add to the pan, with a splash more olive oil if needed. Fry for a couple of minutes to reheat. Season well.
6. Add the dressing to the bowl and coat everything.

Ingredients

- 3 Eggs

Method

Schezwan Chicken Pie 
mubina_18

1 and 1/2 cup shredded chicken 
1 tsp chopped garlic 
1 medium onion chopped 
1 cup thin egg noodles 
1/2 green pepper chopped 
1/2 cup spring onion chopped 
1 tbsp chili garlic sauce 
2 tbsp or more schezwan sauce 
1 tsp vinegar 
1 tsp soya sauce
1 tbsp tomato sauce 
1/2 tsp Worcestershire sauce 
Chopped coriander/ parsley 

Take oil in a pan add chopped onion n cook till soft. 
Then add chopped garlic, shredded chicken and green pepper. 
Now stir all for 2-3 min. 
Then add noodles,chili garlic sauce,schezwan sauce,tomato sauce,vinegar,soya sauce and Worcestershire sauce. 
Mix all well. 
Then lastly add chopped coriander/parsley. 
Roll puff pastry dough. 
Cut into circles n fill it then close with fork. 
Apply egg on it. 
Sprinkle some dry herbs. 
Bake @180.C till golden browns. 
Serve hot with sauce or chutney.

Keto Broccoli Salad

100% effective keto diet program LINK IN BIO @keto_recipes_every_day

INGREDIENTS
FOR THE SALAD
Kosher salt
3 heads broccoli, cut into bite-size pieces
1/2 c. cheddar, shredded
1/4 red onion, thinly sliced
1/4 c. toasted sliced almonds
3 slices bacon, cooked and crumbled
2 tbsp. freshly chopped chives 
FOR THE DRESSING
2/3 c. mayonnaise
3 tbsp. apple cider vinegar
1 tbsp. dijon mustard
Kosher salt
Freshly ground black pepper

If you don't know how to start ketodiet properly or do you want to lose possibly 5-10 lbs in the first week alone with keto Join "Custom Keto Diet". LINK IN BIO @keto_recipes_every_day

DIRECTIONS
In a medium pot or saucepan, bring 6 cups of salted water to a boil. While waiting for the water to boil, prepare a large bowl with ice water.
Add broccoli florets to the boiling water and cook until tender, 1 minute. Remove with a slotted spoon and  immediately place in the prepared bowl of ice water. When cool, spin the broccoli in a salad spinner. You will need to spin it at least twice.
In a medium bowl, whisk to combine dressing ingredients. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Combine all salad ingredients in a large bowl and pour over dressing. Toss until ingredients are combined and fully coated in dressing. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

6 Gran Luchito Soft Tacos Wraps‚Å†

How to make it - ‚Å†
1. Add the Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix onto your chicken breasts with the lime juice, 1 tablespoon of olive oil, a pinch of salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cover with cling film and let it marinate for 20 mins at least.‚Å†
2. In the meantime prepare a quick guacamole. Add the avocado flesh into a bowl and mash it with a fork. Add the onion, jalapeno, extra virgin olive oil, a pinch of salt and black pepper, then mix and set aside.‚Å†
3. In a different bowl prepare a quick pico de gallo. Mix the tomatoes, onion, extra virgin olive oil, lime juice, coriander, salt and pepper.‚Å†
4. Get the barbecue going or heat up a cast-iron skillet with the remaining olive oil. Grill or pan-fry your marinated chicken and let it get a bit of colour on both sides. Finish cooking it covered with a lid, to allow it to cook fully without getting dry.‚Å†
5. Once ready, remove from the heat and cut the chicken into strips with a sharp knife. Serve your chicken with warm Soft Taco Wraps, a good amount of guacamole and some of the pico de gallo. Finally don‚Äôt forget to try some Gran Luchito Salsas!

Why is canned tuna so cheap when fresh tuna is so expensive? 

Tuna salad:
- Tuna+mayo+salt+yogurt+lime
- Red coral lettuce 
- Baby cos lettuce 
- Butterhead lettuce
- Fresh shallots 
- Goji berries 
- Spring onions 
- Hard boiled egg 

Well it basically comes down to what is described as "sushinomics". Tuna that is canned are species that reproduce quickly creating a vast supply (albacore, yellowtail etc.) But are considered less tasty. The ones that are used for sashimi and sushi are the Bluefin tuna which not only require more efforts in catch but are also low in supply. With the fish only reaching reproductive at 8 years and only having a life span of around 40 years, there aren't much to go around. Overfishing has also greatly contributed to the decline in supply of bluefins as they are being caught before being able to reproduce. Lack in regulation will likely lead to extinction of these tasty swimmers. Luckily there are efforts being put forward and the status of bluefin have been reduce from endangered to least concern. Which is great but it needs to be continued because they taste so good ü•∫.

Oh and side note: if you dont want to add alot of mayo to your tuna; sub with unsweetened yogurt, lime and salt. Gives it a fresh taste and adds a 'lil probiotics to you diet.

Last nights dinner - another one of my absolute favouritesü§§ chicken & chorizo jambalayaüòç

Ingredients (serves 4)-
1/2 white onion 
1/2 red pepper 
1/2 yellow pepper 
1 & 1/2 chicken breast diced
75g chorizo 
1 chopped tinned tomatoes 
2 crushed garlics 
200g long grain rice 
1 tbsp Cajun seasoning 
350ml chicken stock 
Salt and pepper to season 

Start by frying the onions, peppers and garlic with a tbsp of olive oil until soft. Then add your diced chicken and Cajun seasoning and cook until browned. Once chicken is brown add in your chorizo and cook for 2-3 minutes. Next you add in the rice, tomatoes and chicken stock, cover and simmer for 25-30minutes until rice is tender.

This peanut butter banana smoothie recipe is DELICIOUS and it‚Äôs really simple to make! Make this quick and healthy snack in less than 5 minutes!

Ingredients
2 bananas
2 cups ice
1 cup milk
1/2 cup greek yogurt plain
2 Tablespoons peanut butter heaping
1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Instructions
Chop the bananas into smaller pieces. Or at the very least, break it in half.
Add all of the ingredients to the blender, adding the ice last.
Blend the ingredients until smooth.
Top your smoothie with melted peanut butter and/or banana pieces. (optional)
Enjoy!

Tempura is a typical Japanese dish that is super versatile. The most well-known dishes are prawns and vegetables in tempura batterüç§. The batter is made in a snap with just flour, corn starch, salt, egg and ice-cold water. 

Did you know that the ice-cold water makes the dish lovely and crispy and it also absorbs less fatü•∂? 

Go on a journey to Japan and don't forget to save this recipe for later!

ùóúÕüùóªÕüùó¥ÕüùóøÕüùó≤Õüùó±Õüùó∂Õüùó≤ÕüùóªÕüùòÅÕüùòÄ
For the dipping sauce: 
175 ml dashi stock 
2 tablespoons soy sauce 
2 tablespoons mirin (Japanese sweet wine) 

For the batter: 
60 g all-purpose flour 
60 g cornstarch 
1 teaspoon kosher salt 
1 large egg, beaten 
175 ml ice-cold club soda 

For frying: 
300 g thinly sliced vegetables 
12 large shrimp, peeled and deveined with tail on 
Vegetable, canola, or peanut oil 

For serving: 
400 g cooked Jasmine rice 

ùó£ÕüùóøÕüùó≤ÕüùóΩÕüùóÆÕüùóøÕüùóÆÕüùòÅÕüùó∂ÕüùóºÕüùóª
Step 1. 
Make the dipping sauce - In a small bowl, whisk together dashi stock, soy sauce, and mirin. Set aside. 

Step 2.
Make the batter - In a medium bowl, stir together flour, cornstarch, and salt. Pour in beaten egg and club soda and stir with chopsticks to combine evenly. Batter will be lumpy. Refrigerate batter till ready to use. 

Step 3. 
Prep for frying - Fill a wok or deep pot halfway with oil and place over medium-high heat. Place a wire rack over a sheet pan lined with paper towels. Heat oil to 190¬∞C or test oil by dropping in a bit of batter. If it sizzles vigorously but doesn‚Äôt brown too quickly you‚Äôre good to go. 

Step 4.
Fry the tempura - Gently dip vegetables and shrimp in tempura and lower into oil. Fry in small batches to avoid overcrowding. Flip and separate items while frying until batter is crisp and golden brown, about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Transfer to wire rack. Allow oil to reheat between batches. 

Step 5.
Serve and enjoy - Divide tempura and rice between four individual plates and serve with a side of dipping sauce.

Ingredients

4 large zucchini thinly sliced lengthwise (I used a mandoline)

1 Tbsp olive oil for brushing + 1 additional Tablespoon for saut√©ing

1 small sweet yellow onion, finely diced

2 fresh garlic cloves, minced

8 oz fresh mushrooms, chopped well

1 tsp dry Italian seasoning

16 ounces high quality marinara sauce

sea salt and fresh ground pepper, to taste

1/3 cup organic ricotta

1 free range egg

1/4 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese

a handful or fresh parsley, finely chopped

1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese

Instructions

Preheat your oven to 375 degrees f. and line a baking tray with parchment paper.

Lay out the zucchini strips on a large cutting board, lightly sprinkle with sea salt and pepper and very lightly brush with 1 Tablespoon of oil.

Bake strips in your preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until slightly tender and easy to roll. Allow them to cool until ready to handle.

Meanwhile, add remaining olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.

Add in the onions, mushrooms, Italian seasonings and cook for 4-5 minutes.

Stir in 3/4 of the marinara sauce and simmer your mushroom sauce for about 4 minutes, or until slightly reduced.

Filipino Chicken Noodle Soup (Sopas). Creamy soup with shredded chicken, hot dogs, and macaroni!!!! 

Ingredients & Recipe
1-2 pieces of boned in chicken breast
3 pieces hot dogs, sliced
6 cups water or broth
1 chicken bouillon
1 small onion
2 cloves of garlic, minced 
2 cups elbow pasta
1 carrot, julienned 
1 celery, sliced
1/2 cup cabbage
2 cup milk
1 tbsp fish sauce
1 tbsp cooking oil
Salt and pepper

1. In a large pot, heat oil under medium high heat. 
2. Saut√© onions and garlic for 2-3 minutes. 
3. Add chicken breasts, seasoning with salt and pepper, searing all sides. 
4. Add water, bouillon, and fish sauce. 
5. Under low medium heat, cook chicken for 2 hours. Skimming off scum. 
6. While chicken is cooking heat a small pan and toast macaroni just until it turns light brown. Remove from heat and set aside. 
7. Remove chicken and shred meat, discarding bones and skin. 
8. Place shredded chicken and hot dogs back into pot. 
9. Add celery, carrots, and macaroni cooking for an additional 7 minutes. 
10. Add cabbage and milk, cooking for an additional 5 minutes. 
11. Season with additional salt and pepper as needed. 
12. Serve immediately.

Looking for a fast recipe to make for lunch? This dish is light and can be made in only 25 minutes!

‚ú®Bok Choy with Tamari Sauce‚ú®

Ingredients:
‚úÖ2 lb bok choy, small 
‚úÖ1 Tbs ginger, fresh, minced
‚úÖ 1/4 cup scallions, thinly sliced 
‚úÖ1 1/2 Tbs olive oil, divided ‚úÖ6 Tbs tamari sauce 
‚úÖ1 Tbs hemp seeds 

Directions:
Prep : 
1. Trim bok choy bottoms and cut in half lengthwise. 
2. Mince ginger. 
3. Slice scallions. 

Make :
1. Coat bottom of pan with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil, over medium-high heat. When hot, lay bok choy in single layer, cut side down (do not overcrowd). Add 2 tablespoons water and cover about 2 minutes. 

2. Lift out of pan, drain, and place on platter. Remove water from pan and repeat with remaining bok choy. Leave residual water in pan. 

3. Add 1 tablespoon oil and ginger to pan and cook, stirring over high 
heat until ginger is browned. Remove from heat and add tamari sauce. 

4. Pour sauce over bok choy, sprinkle with scallions and hemp seeds.

‚ú®What‚Äôs important is that a dough like this can freeze easily so it can be prepped in advance & placed in the fridge for up to 2 days, anything longer may dry it out.
