üå∂Ô∏èüçùüçÖ CHILLI BUTTER TOMATO SPAGHETTI üçÖüçùüå∂Ô∏è Long time no pasta, so just dropping by with a taste of the Med right here ü§§ü§§ A fresh tomato sauce, simmered with garlic and chilli, lotttts of butter, and served with fresh pasta. So much flavour with (mostly) store cupboard ingredients, and ready in 20 - perfect for summer evenings ‚òÄÔ∏è‚òÄÔ∏è I like mine extra saucy and extra buttery, so feel free to bump up your ingredients to suit your taste üëåüèºüëåüèº

Chilli Butter Tomato Spaghetti (serves 2):

150g spaghetti
50g unsalted butter
1/2 red onion, finely chopped
350g cherry/baby plum tomatoes, halved
2 x garlic cloves, sliced
1/2 x teaspoon sea salt (may need more, adjust to taste)
1/2 x teaspoon chilli flakes
1 x tablespoon apple cider vinegar (I used @willysacv)
1/2 teaspoon sugar
Freshly cracked black pepper
Small handful parsley, chopped
50g Parmesan, grated

Cook spaghetti according to pack instructions. Save a ladle of pasta water for the sauce.

On a medium high heat, add the butter to a large saucepan and gently fry the onions for 2-3 minutes. Add the tomato halves and fry for 4-5 minutes. Add the garlic, ACV, sugar, salt, chilli, and continue to cook until the tomatoes soften and release their juices (about another 5-10 minutes). Squish the tomatoes with the back of a wooden spoon to break apart. Add enough reserved pasta water to loosen the sauce (about 50ml), the cooked spaghetti, half the parmesan and the parsley, and combine well. Season with pepper, more salt if required, and serve with the remaining parmesan on top üëåüèºüëåüèº

#Repost @plantbasedrd

No fancy equipment needed and if you use a can of lentils this comes together in 20 minutes. I love to prep these lentils in advance for the week because they are so easy to sprinkle into meals and keep well. And if you don‚Äôt want to chop veggies for your bowl just swap for your favorite bagged salad mix and top with the lentil walnut taco meat. üòå

Lentil Walnut ‚ÄòMeat‚Äô
1, 15 oz can small brown or black lentils, rinsed and drained (salted can preferred)
1/2 cup chopped unsalted walnuts
1/3 cup chopped roasted unsalted sunflower seeds
1 1/2 tbsp adobo sauce from a can of chipotle peppers
1 tsp soy sauce
1 tsp each garlic powder, smoked paprika, chili powder
1/2 tsp ground cumin
1/2 tsp onion powder
Salt and pepper to taste

Salad Base
1 head Romaine Lettuce, shredded
1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved or quartered
1 cup frozen fire roasted corn, thawed
1 red bell pepper, diced
1/3 cup cilantro, roughly chopped (optional)
Juice of half a lime

Chipotle Yogurt Dressing
1/4 cup plain, unsweetened plant-based yogurt
1 1/2 tbsp adobo sauce from a can of chipotle peppers
2 tsp maple syrup
Zest and juice of half a lime

Seasoned Lentils. Add your lentils to a small bowl with the chopped walnuts, sunflower seeds, adobo sauce, soy sauce, spices and toss together then adjust salt to your liking.

Salad Base. To a large salad bowl or mixing bowl add the lettuce, tomatoes, corn, bell pepper and cilantro then season well with a pinch of salt, pepper and lime juice then toss together to combine.

Chipotle Yogurt Dressing. Add the remaining dressing ingredients to a cup and mix well until smooth then add a pinch of salt to taste

Assemble. Add the seasoned lentils on top of the salad base, then add the yogurt dressing before serving.

INGREDIENTS
.

INSTRUCTIONS
.
In a large pot, heat 1 TBS of olive oil.

Polenta porridge with hazelnuts and banana is a great way to mix up your breakfast routine!

If you don‚Äôt have 45 minutes to make breakfast, that‚Äôs ok. It makes for a great meal prep dish!

If you‚Äôve never tried polenta this is a great starter recipe. It‚Äôs an Italian porridge that has a low-fat content and high in complex carbs.

This polenta porridge with hazelnuts and banana is easy to make, nutritious, and extremely tasty! The flavors combine perfectly into a delicious bowl of amazing goodness. You can also substitute the banana with other berries or fruits of your choice.

‚ú® Prep Time: 5 min | Cook Time: 40 min | Serves: 4 ‚ú®

Ingredients
2 cups of water
1/4 teaspoon salt
1/4 teaspoon cinnamon
1/2 cup coarse stone-ground polenta
3 tablespoons honey, divided
3/4 cup of plain greek yogurt
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 banana for topping (blueberries, raspberries, kiwi, and blackberries are also good choices)
¬Ω cup of natural roasted hazelnuts

Instructions
1Ô∏è‚É£Bring the water to a boil.
2Ô∏è‚É£Stir in the salt and slowly whisk in the polenta. Keep stirring so that no clumps form.
3Ô∏è‚É£Add 1 1/2 tablespoons of honey.
4Ô∏è‚É£Reduce heat to a simmer.
5Ô∏è‚É£Simmer for at least 30-35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
6Ô∏è‚É£When the polenta begins to pull away from the sides as you stir, then you know it is done.
7Ô∏è‚É£Remove from heat and whisk in 3/4 cup of yogurt, cinnamon, and the vanilla.
8Ô∏è‚É£Top with remaining honey, sliced banana (or berries of choice), and natural roasted hazelnuts.

Soy Miso Beef
P 48 | F 11 | C 43
470 Calories

180g Diced Lean Beef
2tsp (10ml) Soy Sauce
1tsp (5g) Miso Paste
5g Sesame Oil
1tsp Fresh Ginger (minced)
1 x Garlic (minced)
70g Bok Choy
40g Broccolini
125g Cooked Rice

Season beef with salt and pepper. Mix soy sauce, miso, sesame oil, ginger, and garlic together then pour over the beef and coat evenly.
Using a pan on high heat, stir fry the beef in 2 batches to ensure it cooks crispy, avoid too much liquid from over crowding in the pan. Cook for 3-5 minutes to taste. 
Set aside, clean the wok, then on high heat stir fry the broccolini for 4 minutes. Add the bok choy and a splash of water, cook for 1 minute for perfect crunchy vegetables.
Serve with rice and top with spring onions/chilli to taste.

This peanut butter banana smoothie recipe is DELICIOUS and it‚Äôs really simple to make! Make this quick and healthy snack in less than 5 minutes!

Ingredients
2 bananas
2 cups ice
1 cup milk
1/2 cup greek yogurt plain
2 Tablespoons peanut butter heaping
1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Instructions
Chop the bananas into smaller pieces. Or at the very least, break it in half.
Add all of the ingredients to the blender, adding the ice last.
Blend the ingredients until smooth.
Top your smoothie with melted peanut butter and/or banana pieces. (optional)
Enjoy!

Health is a factor that troubles women more than men, given that they undergo periodic menstruation and pregnancy.

Gynecological issues, for instance, have always been a focus of study when it comes to adversities faced by women. What can be done? To start with, recognizing the adversity of climate change and its impact on women is important. More individuals from gender minorities should be included in the policy and decision-making processes. This will raise general awareness and meet better standards of climate adaptation policies.

Roasted Vegetable Lentil Bowl
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî-
Now the weather has cooled slightly (thank goodness), warmer dishes are back on the menu! 

Ingredients (2-3 servings): 
1 cup of Puy lentils 
1 bay leaf
1 garlic clove 
1 vegetable stock cube
-
1 aubergine 
1 courgette 
1tbsp capers 
1tbsp chopped sun-dried tomatoes
2 cherry tomatoes - chopped 
2tbsp chopped parsley 
30g feta 
1tbsp za‚Äôatar 
-
2tbsp extra virgin olive oil 
1tbsp red wine vinegar 
1tsp sumac 

Wash the lentils gently, drain water and place into a saucepan with the bay leaf, crushed garlic clove and veggie stock cube. Fill with 1 cup of water, bring to the boil then turn down to a simmer with a lid on. Cook until the water has absorbed and the lentils are cooked through. 

Meanwhile, heat your oven to 180 degrees. Chop the aubergine and courgette into same size chunks. Coat with 1tbsp of olive oil and the za‚Äôatar spices. Roast for 25-30 minutes stirring half way.

Assemble the warm salad with all of the extra ingredients above and dress with a mix of extra virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar and sumac.

Chili Chargrilled Corn & Mushrooms Salad 
.
Delicious chargrilled flavors with some sweet corn and meaty mushrooms: this meat free salad is balanced, complete, colorful and healthy. Summer in a plate, ideal for a weeknight! 
‚Äî‚Äî 
‚è±: 15 minutes 
‚Äî‚Äî
Serves 2 
INGREDIENTS
* 2 corn on the cob, kernels cut off 
* 4 big flat mushrooms, sliced 
* 20g jalape√±o pepper‚Äôs slices 
* 1 avocado
* 2 tsp green Tabasco 
* 100g rocket salad 
* 1 tbsp olive oil 
* Dressing: 
 * 1 tbsp Dijon mustard
 * 1 tbsp honey 
 * 1 tbsp cider vinegar
 * 1 tbsp olive oil 
 * 2 garlic cloves, crushed 
‚Äî‚Äî
METHOD
Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil on a griddle pan, on medium heat, then sear the mushrooms slices on these for 5 minutes on each side.
In the meantime, in a non sticky frying pan, chargrill the corn kernels on medium heat, tossing firmly and regularly to ensure homogeneous cooking and coloring. (Should take 8-10 minutes)
Plate the salad, top with the corn, add the avocado, drizzle the Tabasco on the avocado, lay the mushrooms and jalape√±o slices, drizzle the dressing all over and serve while still lukewarm.
‚Äî‚Äî

Ingredients - ‚Å†
Chicken:‚Å†

Salt and freshly ground black pepper (for seasoning)‚Å†
‚Å†
Guacamole:‚Å†
2 ripe avocados‚Å†
¬Ω red onion (finely diced)‚Å†

‚Å†

‚Å†
To Serve:‚Å†
6 Gran Luchito Soft Tacos Wraps‚Å†
‚Å†
How to make it - ‚Å†
1. Add the Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix onto your chicken breasts with the lime juice, 1 tablespoon of olive oil, a pinch of salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cover with cling film and let it marinate for 20 mins at least.‚Å†
2. In the meantime prepare a quick guacamole. Add the avocado flesh into a bowl and mash it with a fork. Add the onion, jalapeno, extra virgin olive oil, a pinch of salt and black pepper, then mix and set aside.‚Å†
3. In a different bowl prepare a quick pico de gallo. Mix the tomatoes, onion, extra virgin olive oil, lime juice, coriander, salt and pepper.‚Å†
4. Get the barbecue going or heat up a cast-iron skillet with the remaining olive oil. Grill or pan-fry your marinated chicken and let it get a bit of colour on both sides. Finish cooking it covered with a lid, to allow it to cook fully without getting dry.‚Å†
5. Once ready, remove from the heat and cut the chicken into strips with a sharp knife. Serve your chicken with warm Soft Taco Wraps, a good amount of guacamole and some of the pico de gallo. Finally don‚Äôt forget to try some Gran Luchito Salsas!

INGREDIENTS

8 Coles Australian Free Range Eggs

METHOD
Step 1
Heat a greased 20cm (base measurement) ovenproof non-stick frying pan over medium heat. Add one-quarter of the potato. Cook for 1 min each side or until light golden and tender. Transfer to a plate. Repeat in 3 more batches with remaining potato.
Step 2
Meanwhile, cook the peas in a medium saucepan of boiling water until tender. Drain well.
Step 3
Lightly whisk the eggs in a medium bowl. Season.
Step 4
Preheat grill on medium. Arrange half the potato over the base of the frying pan. Top with half the peas and half the goat‚Äôs cheese. Continue layering with the remaining potato, peas and goat‚Äôs cheese. Pour over the egg and gently swirl the pan to cover the potato mixture. Cook over medium heat for 6 mins or until almost set.
Step 5
Cook under grill for 5 mins or until just set. Cut into wedges. Serve with salad leaves.

Ingredients

4 large zucchini thinly sliced lengthwise (I used a mandoline)

1 Tbsp olive oil for brushing + 1 additional Tablespoon for saut√©ing

1 small sweet yellow onion, finely diced

2 fresh garlic cloves, minced

8 oz fresh mushrooms, chopped well

1 tsp dry Italian seasoning

16 ounces high quality marinara sauce

sea salt and fresh ground pepper, to taste

1/3 cup organic ricotta

1 free range egg

1/4 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese

a handful or fresh parsley, finely chopped

1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese

Instructions

Preheat your oven to 375 degrees f. and line a baking tray with parchment paper.

Lay out the zucchini strips on a large cutting board, lightly sprinkle with sea salt and pepper and very lightly brush with 1 Tablespoon of oil.

Bake strips in your preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until slightly tender and easy to roll. Allow them to cool until ready to handle.

Meanwhile, add remaining olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.

Add in the onions, mushrooms, Italian seasonings and cook for 4-5 minutes.

Nou dan heb ik iets leuks voor jou van Every mag ik jou op je bestelling 10% korting geven. 
Ga naar de website van EVERY en vul daar de kortingscode in:

of ga naar mijn story en klik op de link. 

Ben benieuwd of jij net zo enthousiast word als mij.
